# Phase 2: Linux File System Deep Dive

## Key Linux Directories

| Directory | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `/`       | Root directory; starting point of the filesystem |
| `/bin`   | Essential binaries for all users |
| `/sbin`  | System binaries for administrative tasks |
| `/usr`   | User applications, libraries, and shared data (`/usr/bin`, `/usr/lib`, `/usr/share`) |
| `/etc`   | Configuration files for system and services |
| `/var`   | Variable data: logs, caches, mail, databases |
| `/tmp`   | Temporary files, usually cleared on reboot |
| `/home`  | User home directories |
| `/lib` & `/lib64` | Shared libraries and kernel modules |
| `/boot`  | Bootloader files, kernel images |
| `/dev`   | Device files for hardware & virtual devices |
| `/proc`  | Virtual filesystem with kernel & process info |
| `/sys`   | Kernel device information |
| `/opt`   | Optional software packages |

